Given <italic>n</italic> points in the plane, we present algorithms for finding maximum perimeter or area convex <italic>k</italic>-gons with vertices <italic>k</italic> of the given <italic>n</italic> points. Our algorithms work in linear space and time <italic>O</italic>(<italic>kn</italic>lg <italic>n</italic> + <italic>n</italic> lg <supscrupt>2</supscrupt><italic>n</italic>). For the special case <italic>k</italic> -&-equil; 3 we give <italic>O</italic> (<italic>n</italic>lg<italic>n</italic>) algorithms for these problems. Several related issues are discussed.